Hadarezer: Hadadezer, הדדעזר \[Strong's H1909\], in the parallel
passage, seems an evident mistake for הדרעזר \[Strong's H1928\],
Hadarezer; for the LXX and Vulgate there, as here, read Αδρααζαρ,
Adarezer. The difference arises from the mistake of a ר, raish, for a ד,
daleth, two letters very similar. [Sa2
8:3](../../../bib/kjv/sa2008.htm#003.md), Hadadezer

